                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/8–647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Wedemeyer</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="92" xml:id="d576fn1">Telegram transmitted via Nanking, August 6.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Nanking</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1947-08-06">August 6, 1947</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>47. There has been indication that the British are lending moral and possibly
                    monetary support to Separatist movement represented by General Li Chi-sen
                    presently located in Hongkong. It is suggested that appropriate agencies be set
                    in motion with a view to clarification.</p>
            </div>
